arrayMgrSoftwareVersion.name: arrayMgrSoftwareVersion
arrayMgrSoftwareVersion.description: Version information for the Dell OpenManage Array Manager software.

arrayMgrGlobalStatus.name: arrayMgrGlobalStatus
arrayMgrGlobalStatus.description: Global health information for the subsystem managed by the Dell Array Manager software. This global status is customized for HP OpenView. Other applications should refer to the agentSystemGlobalStatus entry in the globalData object group. Possible values: 1: Critical 2: Warning 3: Normal 4: Unknown

arrayMgrSoftwareManufacturer.name: arrayMgrSoftwareManufacturer
arrayMgrSoftwareManufacturer.description: Manufacturer information for the Dell Array Manager software.

arrayMgrSoftwareProduct.name: arrayMgrSoftwareProduct
arrayMgrSoftwareProduct.description: Product information for the Dell Array Manager software.

arrayMgrSoftwareDescription.name: arrayMgrSoftwareDescription
arrayMgrSoftwareDescription.description: Product Description for the Dell Array Manager software.

arrayMgrDisplayName.name: arrayMgrDisplayName
arrayMgrDisplayName.description: Name of this agent for display purposes.

arrayMgrDescription.name: arrayMgrDescription
arrayMgrDescription.description: A short description of this agent such as <The Dell Storage Consolidation SNMP Agent>.

arrayMgrAgentVendor.name: arrayMgrAgentVendor
arrayMgrAgentVendor.description: The name of the agent software manufacturer.

arrayMgrAgentVersion.name: arrayMgrAgentVersion
arrayMgrAgentVersion.description: Version information for the Dell OpenManage Array Manager software.

agentSystemGlobalStatus.name: agentSystemGlobalStatus
agentSystemGlobalStatus.description: Global health information for the subsystem managed by the Dell Array Manager software. This global status should be used by applications other than HP OpenView. HP OpenView should refer to the arrayMgrGlobalStatus in the root level object group. This is a rollup for the entire agent including any monitored devices. The status is intended to give initiative to a snmp monitor to get further data when this status is abnormal. Possible values: 1: Normal 2: Warning 3: Non-critical Error 4: Failure 5: Unknown

agentLastGlobalStatus.name: agentLastGlobalStatus
agentLastGlobalStatus.description: The the previous global status of the system managed by the Dell Array Manager software. Possible values: 1: Normal 2: Warning 3: Non-critical Error 4: Failure 5: Unknown

agentTimeStamp.name: agentTimeStamp
agentTimeStamp.description: The last time that the agent values have been updated. Universal time in sec since UTC 1/1/70.

agentGetTimeout.name: agentGetTimeout
agentGetTimeout.description: Suggested timeout value in milliseconds for how long the SNMP getter should wait while attempting to poll the SNMP agent.

agentModifiers.name: agentModifiers
agentModifiers.description: Agent functional modifiers, when set the modifier is active. Bit definitions: Bit 3: agent in debug mode. All other bits are product specific

agentRefreshRate.name: agentRefreshRate
agentRefreshRate.description: Rate in seconds at which the agent cached data is being updated.

agentHostname.name: agentHostname
agentHostname.description: The fully qualified network hostname of the host where the agent is running.

agentIPAddress.name: agentIPAddress
agentIPAddress.description: The IP Address of the host where the agent is running and at which the SNMP agent can be contacted.

agentSoftwareStatus.name: agentSoftwareStatus
agentSoftwareStatus.description: Status of the Array Manager Database service software. 1: Database Up - Communication with the database is possible for SNMP queries. 2: Database Down - Communication with the database is not possible for SNMP queries.

agentAmSnmpVersion.name: agentAmSnmpVersion
agentAmSnmpVersion.description: Version of the Array Manager SNMP extension agent for Windows, SNMP provider for Netware.

agentAmMibVersion.name: agentAmMibVersion
agentAmMibVersion.description: Version of the Array Manager MIB.

providerNumber.name: providerNumber
providerNumber.description: Instance number of this provider entry.

providerName.name: providerName
providerName.description: The name of the module that supports either a family of devices or a set of functions.

providerStatus.name: providerStatus
providerStatus.description: The status of this provider. 1: Loaded 2: Failed 3: Unknown

providerVersion.name: providerVersion
providerVersion.description: This version and build number of the provider module.

controllerTable.name: controllerTable
controllerTable.description: A table of managed RAID controllers. The number of entries is related to number of RAID controllers discovered in the system.

controllerEntry.name: controllerEntry
controllerEntry.description: An entry in the table of RAID controllers. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

controllerNumber.name: controllerNumber
controllerNumber.description: Instance number of this controller entry.

controllerName.name: controllerName
controllerName.description: The name of the contoller in this subsystem as represented in Array Manager. Includes the controller type and instance. For example: Perc3/QC 1.

controllerVendor.name: controllerVendor
controllerVendor.description: The controller's (re)seller's name. For Dell controllers this will = Dell.

controllerType.name: controllerType
controllerType.description: The type of this controller: 1: SCSI 2: PV660F 3: PV662F 4: IDE (Integrated/Intelligent Drive Electronics)

controllerState.name: controllerState
controllerState.description: The status of this controller's subsystem (which includes any devices connected to it.) Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready 2: Failed 3: Online 4: Offline 6: Degraded

controllerSeverity.name: controllerSeverity
controllerSeverity.description: Seriousness of the controller state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

controllerRebuildRateInPercent.name: controllerRebuildRateInPercent
controllerRebuildRateInPercent.description: The percent of the compute cycles dedicated to rebuilding failed array disks.

controllerCacheSizeInMB.name: controllerCacheSizeInMB
controllerCacheSizeInMB.description: The controller's current amount of cache memory in megabytes. If this size is 0, it is less than a megabyte.

controllerCacheSizeInBytes.name: controllerCacheSizeInBytes
controllerCacheSizeInBytes.description: The controller's current amount of cache memory that is less than a megabyte. This combined with the controllerCacheSizeInMB will be the total amount of memory.

controllerPhysicalDeviceCount.name: controllerPhysicalDeviceCount
controllerPhysicalDeviceCount.description: Number of physical devices on the controller channel including both disks and the controller.

controllerLogicalDeviceCount.name: controllerLogicalDeviceCount
controllerLogicalDeviceCount.description: Number of virtual disks on the controller.

controllerPartnerStatus.name: controllerPartnerStatus
controllerPartnerStatus.description: Indicates availability of the redundant controller in a redundant configuration. Booting: Controller is powering up. OK: Controller is in fully redundant status. Inserted: Controller is there, but not acting as a partner. Kill Partner Command Received: Failed: UnknownStatus: SCSI Comm Failure:

controllerHostPortCount.name: controllerHostPortCount
controllerHostPortCount.description: The number of host ports on this controller. Host Port: An active fibre port connected to an arbitrated loop. The port may be opened by an initiator on the loop and process i/o requests.

controllerMemorySizeInMB.name: controllerMemorySizeInMB
controllerMemorySizeInMB.description: Size of memory in megabytes on the controller. If this size is 0, it is less than a megabyte.

controllerMemorySizeInBytes.name: controllerMemorySizeInBytes
controllerMemorySizeInBytes.description: Size of memory on the controller that is less than a megabyte. This combined with the controllerMemorySizeInMB will be the total size of the memory.

controllerDriveChannelCount.name: controllerDriveChannelCount
controllerDriveChannelCount.description: The number of redundant drive channels for the controller.

controllerFaultTolerant.name: controllerFaultTolerant
controllerFaultTolerant.description: Indicates whether the controller is enabled to be fault tolerant. 0: no 1: yes

controllerC0Port0WWN.name: controllerC0Port0WWN
controllerC0Port0WWN.description: World Wide name for the first port on controller 0.

controllerC0Port0Name.name: controllerC0Port0Name
controllerC0Port0Name.description: The unique value/name assigned to the controller's first active port.

controllerC0Port0ID.name: controllerC0Port0ID
controllerC0Port0ID.description: The controller's preferred host port/loopid as specified by controller option 'hard loop id' for its first port.

controllerC0Target.name: controllerC0Target
controllerC0Target.description: The controller in slot 0 (it should always be the master controller.)

controllerC0Channel.name: controllerC0Channel
controllerC0Channel.description: Channel number of the controller's first port. Channel: A path for the transfer of data and controller information between the host or the physical disk drives and the controller.

controllerC0OSController.name: controllerC0OSController
controllerC0OSController.description: Manufacturer's identification of controller on first port.

controllerC0BatteryState.name: controllerC0BatteryState
controllerC0BatteryState.description: Current state of battery on the controller's first port. Possible values: 0: Unknown 1: OK (present and operational) 2: Failed (cannot hold charge or cannot be recharged) 7: Reconditioning (PV660 Only) 9: High 10: Low 12: Charging 21: Missing (Adaptec Only)

controllerC1Port0WWN.name: controllerC1Port0WWN
controllerC1Port0WWN.description: World Wide name for the first port on controller 1.

controllerC1Port0Name.name: controllerC1Port0Name
controllerC1Port0Name.description: The unique value/name assigned to the controller's second active port.

controllerC1Port0ID.name: controllerC1Port0ID
controllerC1Port0ID.description: The controller's preferred host port/loopid as specified by controller option 'hard loop id' for its second port. (Value of 255 = C1 controller not there)

controllerC1Target.name: controllerC1Target
controllerC1Target.description: The controller in slot 1. (Value of 255 = controller not there)

controllerC1Channel.name: controllerC1Channel
controllerC1Channel.description: Channel number of the controller's second port. Channel: A path for the transfer of data and controller information between the host or the physical disk drives and the controller. (Value of 255 = controller not there)

controllerC1OSController.name: controllerC1OSController
controllerC1OSController.description: Manufacturer's identification of controller on second port. (Value of 255 = controller not there)

controllerC1BatteryState.name: controllerC1BatteryState
controllerC1BatteryState.description: Current state of battery on the controller's second port. Possible values: 0: Unknown 1: OK (present and operational) 2: Failed (cannot hold charge or cannot be recharged) 7: Reconditioning (PV660 Only) 9: High 10: Low 12: Charging 21: Missing (Adaptec Only)

controllerNodeWWN.name: controllerNodeWWN
controllerNodeWWN.description: Used as the node name for the storage subsystem.

controllerC0Port1WWN.name: controllerC0Port1WWN
controllerC0Port1WWN.description: World Wide name for the second port on controller 0.

controllerC1Port1WWN.name: controllerC1Port1WWN
controllerC1Port1WWN.description: World Wide name for the second port on controller 1.

controllerBatteryChargeCount.name: controllerBatteryChargeCount
controllerBatteryChargeCount.description: The number of charges that have been applied to the battery on this controller.

channelTable.name: channelTable
channelTable.description: A table of controller channels. The number of entries is related to number of channels supported in a RAID controllers. Perc2 RAID controller supports a max of 4 channels per controller. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent.

channelEntry.name: channelEntry
channelEntry.description: An entry in the channel table. A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

channelNumber.name: channelNumber
channelNumber.description: Instance number of this channel entry.

channelName.name: channelName
channelName.description: The name of the channel as represented in Array Manager. The name will include the word channel and the instance. For example: Channel 1

channelState.name: channelState
channelState.description: The current state of this channel. Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready - The I/O has resumed. 2: Failed 3: Online 4: Offline - The I/O has paused. 6: Degraded

channelSeverity.name: channelSeverity
channelSeverity.description: Seriousness of the channel state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

channelTermination.name: channelTermination
channelTermination.description: The type of SCSI termination on this channel. Termination is required for proper operation of this channel. 1: Wide Termination (16 bit) 2: Narrow Termination (8 bit) 3: Not Terminated

channelSCSIID.name: channelSCSIID
channelSCSIID.description: The SCSI ID of the controller to which the channel belongs.

enclosureNumber.name: enclosureNumber
enclosureNumber.description: Instance number of the enclosure entry.

enclosureName.name: enclosureName
enclosureName.description: The enclosure's name as represented in Array Manager.

enclosureState.name: enclosureState
enclosureState.description: The state of the controller. Possible states: 0 : Unknown 1 : Ready 2 : Failed 3 : Online 4 : Offline 6 : Degraded 55: Communication Lost

enclosureSeverity.name: enclosureSeverity
enclosureSeverity.description: Seriousness of the enclosure state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

enclosureID.name: enclosureID
enclosureID.description: For fibre channel - The number of the enclosure in the subsystem. For SCSI - The SCSI address of the processor.

enclosureProcessorVersion.name: enclosureProcessorVersion
enclosureProcessorVersion.description: Firmware version of the enclosure's processor. For Fibre Channel only.

enclosureServiceTag.name: enclosureServiceTag
enclosureServiceTag.description: Enclosure identification used when consulting customer support.

enclosureAssetTag.name: enclosureAssetTag
enclosureAssetTag.description: Customer definable asset tag for the enclosure.

enclosureAssetName.name: enclosureAssetName
enclosureAssetName.description: Customer definable asset name of the enclosure.

enclosureSplitBusPartNumber.name: enclosureSplitBusPartNumber
enclosureSplitBusPartNumber.description: The enclosure's split bus part number.

enclosureProductID.name: enclosureProductID
enclosureProductID.description: The enclosure's product identification. This also corresponds to the enclosure type.

enclosureKernelVersion.name: enclosureKernelVersion
enclosureKernelVersion.description: The version of the enclosure's kernel (Dell PV200S, PV201S, PV210S, and PV211S only.)

enclosureType.name: enclosureType
enclosureType.description: The type of this enclosure. Possible values: 1: Internal 2: Dell PV200S (PV201S) 3: Dell PV210S (PV211S) 4: Dell PV220S (PV221S) 5: Dell PV660F 6: Dell PV224F 7: Dell PV660F / PV224F

enclosureConfig.name: enclosureConfig
enclosureConfig.description: The current configuration of the enclosure's backplane. Possible values: 1: Joined 2: Split Bus 3: Clustered

enclosureChannelNumber.name: enclosureChannelNumber
enclosureChannelNumber.description: The channel number, or bus, to which the enclosure is connected.

enclosureAlarm.name: enclosureAlarm
enclosureAlarm.description: The current status of the enclosure's alarm (PV220S, and PV221S only.) Possible values: 1: Off 2: On

enclosureBackplanePartNumber.name: enclosureBackplanePartNumber
enclosureBackplanePartNumber.description: The part number of the enclosure's backplane.

enclosureSCSIID.name: enclosureSCSIID
enclosureSCSIID.description: The SCSI ID of the controller to which this enclosure is attached.

arrayDiskTable.name: arrayDiskTable
arrayDiskTable.description: A table of managed Array Disks. The number of entries is related to number of Array Disks discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent.

arrayDiskEntry.name: arrayDiskEntry
arrayDiskEntry.description: An entry in the Array Disk table . A row in this table cannot be created or deleted by SNMP operations on columns of the table.

arrayDiskNumber.name: arrayDiskNumber
arrayDiskNumber.description: Instance number of this array disk entry.

arrayDiskName.name: arrayDiskName
arrayDiskName.description: The name of the array disk as represented in Array Manager.

arrayDiskState.name: arrayDiskState
arrayDiskState.description: The current state of the array disk. Possible states: 0: Unknown 1: Ready - Available for use, but no RAID configuration has been assigned. 2: Failed - Not operational. 3: Online - Operational. RAID configuration has been assigned. 4: Offline - The drive is not available to the RAID controller. 6: Degraded - Refers to a fault-tolerant array/virtual disk that has a failed disk. 7: Recovering - Refers to state of recovering from bad blocks on disks. 11: Removed - Indicates that array disk has been removed. 15: Resynching - Indicates one of the following types of disk operations: Transform Type, Reconfiguration, and Check Consistency. 24: Rebuild 25: No Media - CD-ROM or removable disk has no media. 26: Formatting - In the process of formatting. 28: Diagnostics - Diagnostics are running. 35: Initializing: Applies only to virtual disks on PERC, PERC 2/SC, and PERC 2/DC controllers.

arrayDiskSeverity.name: arrayDiskSeverity
arrayDiskSeverity.description: Severity of the array disk state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

arrayDiskProductID.name: arrayDiskProductID
arrayDiskProductID.description: The model number of the array disk.

arrayDiskSerialNo.name: arrayDiskSerialNo
arrayDiskSerialNo.description: The array disk's unique identification number from the manufacturer.

arrayDiskRevision.name: arrayDiskRevision
arrayDiskRevision.description: The firmware version of the array disk.

arrayDiskEnclosureID.name: arrayDiskEnclosureID
arrayDiskEnclosureID.description: The SCSI ID of the enclosure processor to which this array disk belongs.

arrayDiskChannel.name: arrayDiskChannel
arrayDiskChannel.description: The bus to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskLengthInMB.name: arrayDiskLengthInMB
arrayDiskLengthInMB.description: The size in megabytes of the array disk. If this size is 0, it is smaller than a megabyte.

arrayDiskLengthInBytes.name: arrayDiskLengthInBytes
arrayDiskLengthInBytes.description: The size of the array disk in bytes that is less than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskLengthInMB is the total size of the array disk.

arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB.name: arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB
arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB.description: The size in megabytes of the largest contiguous free space on the array disk. If this size is 0, it is less than a megabyte.

arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInByt.name: arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInBytes
arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInByt.description: The size of the largest contiguouis free space on this array disk in bytes that is less than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskLargestContiguousFreeSpaceInMB is the total size of the largest contiguous free space on the array disk.

arrayDiskTargetID.name: arrayDiskTargetID
arrayDiskTargetID.description: The SCSI target ID which this array disk is assigned.

arrayDiskLunID.name: arrayDiskLunID
arrayDiskLunID.description: The array disk's logical unit number.

arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB.name: arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB
arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB.description: The amount in megabytes of the used space on the array disk. If this size is 0, it is smaller than a megabyte.

arrayDiskUsedSpaceInBytes.name: arrayDiskUsedSpaceInBytes
arrayDiskUsedSpaceInBytes.description: The size in bytes of the used space on the array disk that is smaller than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskUsedSpaceInMB is the total amount of used space on the array disk.

arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB.name: arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB
arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB.description: The amount in megabytes of the free space on the array disk. If this size is 0, it is smaller than a megabyte.

arrayDiskFreeSpaceInBytes.name: arrayDiskFreeSpaceInBytes
arrayDiskFreeSpaceInBytes.description: The size in bytes of the free space on the array disk that is smaller than a megabyte. This size plus the arrayDiskFreeSpaceInMB is the total amount of free space on the array disk.

arrayDiskBusType.name: arrayDiskBusType
arrayDiskBusType.description: The bus type of the array disk. Possible values: 1: SCSI 2: IDE 3: Fibre Channel 4: SSA 6: USB

arrayDiskSpareState.name: arrayDiskSpareState
arrayDiskSpareState.description: The status of the array disk as a spare. Possible states: 1: disk is a member of a virtual disk 2: disk is a member of a disk group 3: disk is a global hot spare 4: disk is a dedicated hot spare

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionTable.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionTable
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between array disks, their enclosure, and their associated controller. For each object in the table, its object number corresponds to an instance number in the appropriate MIB table for that object where all of the object properties can be found.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionNumber.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this array disk connection entry. This table shows the array disk to SCSI or Fibre Channel enclosure relationship.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNam.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskName
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNam.description: The name of the array disk in this connection as represented in Array Manager.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNum.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionArrayDiskNum.description: The instance number of the array disk in the arrayDiskTable in this connection.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNam.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureName
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNam.description: The name of the enclosure as represented in Array Manager to which this array disk belongs.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNum.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionEnclosureNum.description: The instance number in the enclosureTable of the enclosure to which this array disk belongs.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNa.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerName
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNa.description: The name of the controller as represented in Array Manager to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNu.name: arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNumber
arrayDiskEnclosureConnectionControllerNu.description: The instance number in the controllerTable of the controller to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionTable.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionTable
arrayDiskChannelConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between array disks, their channel, and their associated controller. For each object in the table, its object number corresponds to an instance number in the appropriate MIB table for that object where all of the object properties can be found.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionNumber.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this array disk connection entry. This table shows the array disk to SCSI channel relationship. There is no enclosure service processor associated with these array disks.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskName.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskName
arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskName.description: The name of the array disk in this connection as represented in Array Manager.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskNumbe.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionArrayDiskNumbe.description: The instance number of the array disk in the arrayDiskTable in this connection.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelName.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelName
arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelName.description: The name of the channel as represented in Array Manager to which is array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelNumber.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionChannelNumber.description: The instance number of the channel in the channelTable to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerName.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerName
arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerName.description: The name of the controller as represented in Array Manager to which this array disk is connected.

arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerNumb.name: arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerNumber
arrayDiskChannelConnectionControllerNumb.description: The instance number in the controllerTable of the controller to which this array disk is connected.

fanNumber.description: Instance number of this fan entry.

fanName.name: fanName
fanName.description: The fan's name as represented in Array Manager.

fanState.name: fanState
fanState.description: Current state of the fan. Possible states: 0 : Unknown 1 : Ready 2 : Failed 3 : Online 4 : Offline 6 : Degraded 55: Communication Lost

fanSeverity.name: fanSeverity
fanSeverity.description: Seiousness of the fan state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

fanProbeMinWarning.name: fanProbeMinWarning
fanProbeMinWarning.description: The minimum value that will force the fan into a warning state.

fanProbeMinCritical.name: fanProbeMinCritical
fanProbeMinCritical.description: The minimum value that will force the fan into an error state.

fanProbeMaxWarning.name: fanProbeMaxWarning
fanProbeMaxWarning.description: The maximum value that will force the fan into a warning state.

fanProbeMaxCritical.name: fanProbeMaxCritical
fanProbeMaxCritical.description: The maximum value that will force the fan into an error state.

fanProbeCurrValue.name: fanProbeCurrValue
fanProbeCurrValue.description: The current speed of the fan.

fan1PartNumber.name: fan1PartNumber
fan1PartNumber.description: The part number of the fan in the enclosure.

fanConnectionTable.name: fanConnectionTable
fanConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between each fan on the managed node and its enclosure. Each enclosure number in the table corresponds to that enclosure instance in the Enclosure Table.

fanConnectionNumber.name: fanConnectionNumber
fanConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this fan connection entry.

fanConnectionFanName.name: fanConnectionFanName
fanConnectionFanName.description: The name of the fan in this connection as represented in Array Manager.

fanConnectionFanNumber.name: fanConnectionFanNumber
fanConnectionFanNumber.description: The instance number of the fan in the fanTable in this connection.

fanConnectionEnclosureName.name: fanConnectionEnclosureName
fanConnectionEnclosureName.description: The name of the enclosure as represented in Array Manager to which this fan belongs.

fanConnectionEnclosureNumber.name: fanConnectionEnclosureNumber
fanConnectionEnclosureNumber.description: The instance number of the enclosure in the enclosureTable to which this fan belongs.

powersupplyNumber.name: powersupplyNumber
powersupplyNumber.description: Instance number of this powersupply entry.

powersupplyName.name: powersupplyName
powersupplyName.description: The power supply's name as represented in Array Manager.

powersupplyState.name: powersupplyState
powersupplyState.description: Current state of the power supply. Possible states: 0 : Unknown 1 : Ready 2 : Failed 55: Communication Lost

powersupplySeverity.name: powersupplySeverity
powersupplySeverity.description: Seriousness of the power supply state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

powersupply1PartNumber.name: powersupply1PartNumber
powersupply1PartNumber.description: The part number of the power supply of the enclosure.

powersupplyConnectionTable.name: powersupplyConnectionTable
powersupplyConnectionTable.description: A table of the connections between each power supply on the managed node and its enclosure. Each enclosure number in the table corresponds to that enclosure instance in the Enclosure Table.

powersupplyConnectionNumber.name: powersupplyConnectionNumber
powersupplyConnectionNumber.description: Instance number of this powersupply connection entry.

powersupplyConnectionPowersupplyName.name: powersupplyConnectionPowersupplyName
powersupplyConnectionPowersupplyName.description: The name of the power supply in this connection as represented in Array Manager.

powersupplyConnectionPowersupplyNumber.name: powersupplyConnectionPowersupplyNumber
powersupplyConnectionPowersupplyNumber.description: This instance number in the powersupplyTable of the power supply in this connection.

powersupplyConnectionEnclosureName.name: powersupplyConnectionEnclosureName
powersupplyConnectionEnclosureName.description: The name of the enclosure to which this power supply is connected as represented in Array Manager.

powersupplyConnectionEnclosureNumber.name: powersupplyConnectionEnclosureNumber
powersupplyConnectionEnclosureNumber.description: The instance number of the enclosure in the enclosureTable to which this power supply is connected.

temperatureNumber.name: temperatureNumber
temperatureNumber.description: Instance number of this temperature probe entry.

temperatureName.name: temperatureName
temperatureName.description: Name of this temperature probe as represented in Array Manager.

temperatureState.name: temperatureState
temperatureState.description: Current state of this temperature probe. Possible states: 0 : Unknown 1 : Ready 2 : Failed 4 : Offline 6 : Degraded 55: Communication Lost

temperatureSeverity.name: temperatureSeverity
temperatureSeverity.description: Seriousness of the temperature probe state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

temperatureProbeUnit.name: temperatureProbeUnit
temperatureProbeUnit.description: The units that will be used to display temperatures for this temperature probe.

temperatureProbeMinWarning.name: temperatureProbeMinWarning
temperatureProbeMinWarning.description: The minimum temperature that will force the probe into a warning state.

temperatureProbeMinCritical.name: temperatureProbeMinCritical
temperatureProbeMinCritical.description: The minimum temperature that will force the probe into an error state.

temperatureProbeMaxWarning.name: temperatureProbeMaxWarning
temperatureProbeMaxWarning.description: The maximum temperature that will force the probe into a warning state.

temperatureProbeMaxCritical.name: temperatureProbeMaxCritical
temperatureProbeMaxCritical.description: The maximum temperature that will force the probe into an error state.

temperatureProbeCurValue.name: temperatureProbeCurValue
temperatureProbeCurValue.description: The current temperature of this probe.

temperatureConnectionTemperatureName.description: The name of the temperature probe in this connection as represented in Array Manager.

temperatureConnectionTemperatureNumber.name: temperatureConnectionTemperatureNumber
temperatureConnectionTemperatureNumber.description: The instance number in the temperatureTable of the temperature probe in this connection.

temperatureConnectionEnclosureName.name: temperatureConnectionEnclosureName
temperatureConnectionEnclosureName.description: The name of the enclosure as represented in Array Manager to which this temperature probe belongs.

temperatureConnectionEnclosureNumber.name: temperatureConnectionEnclosureNumber
temperatureConnectionEnclosureNumber.description: The instance number of the enclosure in the enclosureTable to which this temperature probe belongs.

enclosureManagementModuleTable.name: enclosureManagementModuleTable
enclosureManagementModuleTable.description: A table of managed Enclosure Memory Modules. The number of entries is related to number of Enclosure Memory Modules discovered in the system. The maximum number of entries is implementation dependent.

enclosureManagementModuleNumber.name: enclosureManagementModuleNumber
enclosureManagementModuleNumber.description: Instance number of this enclosure memory module entry.

enclosureManagementModuleName.name: enclosureManagementModuleName
enclosureManagementModuleName.description: Name of this enclosure memory module as represented in Array Manager.

enclosureManagementModuleState.name: enclosureManagementModuleState
enclosureManagementModuleState.description: The state of the enclosure management module. Possible states: 0 : Unknown 1 : Ready 2 : Failed 3 : Online 4 : Offline 6 : Degraded 55: Communication Lost

enclosureManagementModuleSeverity.name: enclosureManagementModuleSeverity
enclosureManagementModuleSeverity.description: Seriousness of the enclosure management module state. Possible values: 0: OK 1: Warning 2: Error 3: Failure

enclosureManagementModulePartNumber.name: enclosureManagementModulePartNumber
